t><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 9:44:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're an INT wiz then enter here...</span><hr size=1> The &quot;mug&quot; you refered too is the Stien of Mogguk.  Depending on server, you can pick one up for about 150pp.  Great boost, gives +10 int.  As for the Staff of the Wheel, I would suggest waiting till 24 for that, when you get your remaining port spells.  The quest takes starts/ends in Everfrost, near the Shaman dot vender out in the plains area.  As for the rods, check out the quest page here, it is the BEST way to do this quest.  Question, I take it you are a human.  Didn't you put your stat bonuses into int???  if not, I would highly recommend starting over.  Int is the most important stat.  For making cash, you can go to WK and kill the bandits there.  Keep all sashes and bronze weapons, destroy all else.  Once filled up, head over to South Qyenos and right outside the Paly guild is a guy that wants the sashes, give them to him for some bronze weapons, then just turn around and sell the weapons right back to him.  Now, if your KOS to Qyenos, and you don't care about faction, head to OOT and sister island (first boat stop going from Freeport to Butcherblock).  Kill the sisters for a purity belt worth 1pp at venders.  Then just go sell them.  Problem is, this will ruin faction with most of Faydwer.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nunarie>Nunarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/01 2:34:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Better Hunting</span><hr size=1> At 20 you can do the Wheel quest just takes a bit longer...I'd recomend unrest...or mistmoore maybe Cazic..but only in a good group.  Other than that get used to being poor till you get around 29.  And if nothing else look up the stien quest..make an inky chanter and do the quest at lvl 8 it should take a day or two to get to that lvl and that is how I got my stien. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utholien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tholien</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/01 3:10:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Better Hunting</span><hr size=1> One question, where did you put your starting stats, my wiz is human and my starting int was still 110 with maxxed int for a human.  If you choose erudian you can start with as high as 142 int, dont know how you only have 90 int with what ever stuff you have on.  You will have a long hard road with that int, but it can still be doable, but I too would think about starting over if I was you.  Your mana pool will be very dismal until you get your int up to respectable levels.<br><br>Tholien Brainburner 55 lvl Enchanter Xev<br>Uieni Dahealer 51 lvl Cleric Xev<br>Kysos Stinger 35 lvl Wiz Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxxxavian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xxxavian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 2:05:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're an INT wiz then enter here...</span><hr size=1> 90 int <br><br>START OVER - do it right <br>Everything into INT<br><br>53 Necro Torv INT 223<br>22 Wizzy Torv INT 192<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=berdug0>berdug0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 9:19:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're an INT wiz then enter here...</span><hr size=1> 90 int...<br><br>I didn't know Ogres can make Wizards.. hehe..<br><br>You're level 20 and it's a tough choice to start over.<br><br>If you haven't made any friends yet, go ahead and start over.  You'll be surprised how much faster you'll get back to 20 since you are a bit more familiar with your hunting spots.<br><br>Start an Erud or Dark Elf and don't mess around scrapping for INT items.  Some people here say do the Quest for this and quest for that... whatever.<br><br>Band of Rodcet Nife - should be easy to get if you have good faction with Surefall and Kaladim.  Otherwise.<br><br>Gold Ear Stud - Yeah Whatever... camped cuburt for 2 hours. Spawned 3 times, no dress.<br><br>At level 30 when I finally needed int, I can afford them (thank god for Teleports).  I went from 142 int to 171 within 1 hour shouting for int items in EC. No questing for 2 to 6 hours for items that only give 3 int. 2 components from staff of the wheel and i'll be at 181.<br><br>Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 9:20:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're an INT wiz then enter here...</span><hr size=1> I hate to be a nay sayer, but you would be better served by starting over. Level 20 should be pretty easy to get back to if you get yout INT up to where it should be. With better INT you would find soloing AND getting groups easier. At this level, you outdamage melee by such huge amounts, most groups should still be impressed by your power. To give you an idea of the HUGE disadvantage you have with your INT - take a look at this -<br><br>Level 20 w/ 90 INT:<br>Total mana: 400 mana (no +mana items included for this)<br>Total damage possible 1 bar mana: 560 (5 flame shock, 1 Icestrike)<br><br>now take an erudite with max skill points into INT with NO OTHER INT EQUIPMENT:<br>Level 20 w/142 INT:<br>Total mana: 608 mana (no +mana items included)<br>Total damage possible 1 bar mana: 880 (8 flame shock)<br><br>As you can see, this is a HUGE difference. Not to mention, by level 20 you should have a robe, some rings, and earrings to get you INT even higher. I don't think 160 INT at level 20 is hard to attain even if you aren't a twink.<br><br>This extra INT would allow you to solo when you can't get a group, or blast a lot more without going oom in a group. Later in life, you will also find that every spot you can open up for resist gear or +mana is helpful. The easier you can get the 200 INT cap the better. At lvl 45, I dont have any INT gear in either ear slot, head slot, shoulders, or hands. And I still have over 200 INT and I don't have any &quot;uber&quot; equipment. Do yourself a favor and reroll a wizard, I think you will be better of and much happier. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 45th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 23 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i><br><span style="font-size: 12px; font-famliy: arial">proud member of Infinity Watch - Terris-Thule server</span></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A> at: 6/5/01 10:26:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uazlinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azlinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 7:38:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.guildmagic.com/pics/6029.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're an INT wiz then enter here...</span><hr size=1> As a very, very financially unsound wizard (meaning I only bought a 3int robe), I managed to cross the 200 int mark at level 30.  I started at 140int as an Erudite, and I would certainly recommend putting all your points into int; I wish I had put those last two points in as well. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=6029">Azlinon Seflarian</a> of <a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/divinesymphony">Divine Symphony</a><br>Guild-Leader<br>Wizard of Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=70.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=70.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=70.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=70.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm2">General Quests<option value="graff